value.title: Vice President Mike Pence postpones Friday appearance to vote in Indianapolis
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence cancels a Friday appearance in Indianapolis to vote early. His office says the trip to cast his ballot will be rescheduled.

value.title: Trump suggests he may hold weekend rallies in Florida, Pennsylvania after receiving green light from doctor
value.excerpt: President Trump told Fox News' Sean Hannity in an exclusive interview Thursday that his campaign is trying to make last-minute arrangements for holding weekend rallies in Florida and Pennsylvania after White House physician Dr. Sean Conley cleared him for public engagements earlier in the day.

value.title: Karen Pence’s office says both sides agreed to no masks at end of debate
Debate commission co-chair defends virtual move after Trump pulls out: 'We will be guided by the medicine'
value.excerpt: Commission on Presidential Debates (CPD) co-chair Frank Fahrenkopf has defended the organization's decision to move the second presidential debate, slated for Oct. 15, to a virtual setting after President Trump dismissed the idea as a "waste" of time.

value.title: Biden says he'll answer court-packing question 'when the election is over'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden again ducked questions Thursday about whether he would seek to add seats to the Supreme Court, telling reporters he would not address the issue until after the November 3 election.

value.title: At debate, Mike Pence didn’t say what he has before: He supports overturning Roe v. Wade
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence artfully sidestepped the chance to talk about banning abortion before a national audience at Wednesday’s debate.

value.title: Kamala Harris vs. Mike Pence takeaways: Coronavirus, ‘I’m speaking’ and California’s cameo
value.excerpt: Aside from the historic nature of Sen. Kamala Harris’ appearance the event in Salt Lake City was so civil that the social media star of the evening was a fly that landed on Vice President Mike Pence’s hair and lingered for more than two minutes.

value.title: Karen Pence's office defends her appearing without a mask at debate
value.excerpt: Second lady Karen Pence’s office defended her appearance on the debate stage Wednesday night without wearing a mask.

value.title: Pence does his best but Harris won't let him explain away Trump's failures
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence tried his best on Wednesday to recast the reality of Donald Trump's presidency, but Sen. Kamala Harris, the Democratic pick for his job, refused to let him spin away the nation's current dire plight during their single debate.

value.title: Rick Santorum cut off female co-panelist Gloria Borger while she was talking about Mike Pence interrupting Kamala Harris at the VP debate
value.excerpt: Pence interrupted Harris twice as often during Wednesday night's vice-presidential debate, prompting criticism from the CNN analyst Borger.

value.title: What Trump's comments about ceasing stimulus-package negotiations mean for future $1,200 payments — in one minute or less
value.excerpt: Confused on all the news around the stimulus talks and Trump's tweets? Catch up on what it all means for the chances of another stimulus check here.

value.title: Kanye West Tweets Video With 'Vote Kanye' Hat on Kamala Harris' Head During VP Debate
value.excerpt: Kanye West's name will appear on ballots in 11 states, but people have wondered whether his presidential campaign is sincere, a spoiler attempt or just a publicity stunt.

value.title: Vice presidential debate: Both Trump, Biden campaign claim victory after Pence, Harris showdown
value.excerpt: Both the Trump campaign and the Biden campaign claimed victory after Wednesday night’s vice presidential debate—with team Trump touting Vice President Pence, saying he is “ready to lead,” and team Biden praising Sen. Kamala Harris for making a “forceful case” for a Biden presidency.

value.title: Former CIA Director Accuses Mike Pence of Lying About Hillary Clinton and Russia During VP Debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence "lied about handwritten notes of mine from 2016 that referenced unsubstantiated Russian allegation about Secretary Clinton" during his debate with Senator Kamala Harris, former CIA Director John Brennan tweeted on Wednesday night.

value.title: Analysis: This is Vice President Mike Pence's answer on a peaceful transfer of power. Read it carefully.
value.excerpt: The vice presidential debate Wednesday night will be remembered more for how the candidates evaded questions than how they answered them.

value.title: AOC to VP Pence: ‘It’s Congresswoman Ocasio-Cortez to you’
value.excerpt: U.S. Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez appeared to be closely watching the vice presidential debate Wednesday night, tweeting several responses to comments by Vice President Mike Pence.

value.title: AOC Corrects Mike Pence During VP Debate: 'It's Congresswoman Ocasio-Cortez to You'
value.excerpt: Cortez tweeted to Vice President Mike Pence as he referred to her as "AOC" during his debate with Senator Kamala Harris. "It's Congresswoman Ocasio-Cortez to you."

value.title: Pence targets Biden over ISIS hostages, brings family of executed aid worker to debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Pence invoked slain ISIS hostage Kayla Mueller on Wednesday as he sought to tout what he described as President Trump’s foreign policy accomplishments in his debate against Sen. Kamala Harris (D-Calif.

value.title: A Fly Landed on Mike Pence
value.excerpt: A local TV news reporter from California clocked the fly’s screen time on Mr. Pence’s head at 2 minutes, 3 seconds. While Mr. Pence spent most of the 90-minute debate avoiding direct questions posed by the moderator,

value.title: Pence attacks Biden for failing to rescue Kayla Mueller, who was held hostage by ISIS.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence brought the parents of Kayla Mueller, the human rights activist who was killed in 2015 by members of the Islamic State in Syria, to the debate hall and attacked Joseph R. Biden Jr.

value.title: An unexpected guest: Fly lands on Mike Pence's head during debate, goes viral
value.excerpt: The fly, which was on Mike Pence's head for several minutes, quickly went viral and created a buzz – pun intended – online.

value.title: Harris says she is a person of faith, 'insulting' to suggest she would knock anyone for religion
value.excerpt: Sen. Kamala Harris invoked her faith during the vice presidential debate to insist that Judge Amy Coney Barrett would be treated fairly on account of her faith during her upcoming confirmation hearings.

value.title: Fact check: Trump's hospital records, weight have not been released
value.excerpt: Social media posts claim President Donald Trump is underrepresenting his weight by nearly 80 pounds. His latest physical results reveal this is false.

value.title: Biden crosses 270 threshold in CNN's Electoral College outlook for first time
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is surging in the battle for the White House with less than four weeks to go until Election Day.

value.title: McDaniel slams Biden over 'despicable' politicization of coronavirus in first interview since positive test
value.excerpt: The coronavirus pandemic has brought out the "worst" in Joe Biden and the Democratic Party, Republican National Committee Chairwoman Ronna McDaniel told "Bill Hemmer Reports" on Wednesday.
